comments.comment:
The problem is that even if we switched to CXF 3.1.x, we still use Camel 2.15.1.redhat-6-2-x which includes repository of CXF 3.0.4.redhat-6-2-x and resolver tries to resolve "jetty" feature with the range [7, 9):

    <feature name="cxf-http-jetty" version="3.0.4.redhat-621083" resolver="(obr)">
 
        <feature version="[3,4)">cxf-http</feature>
 
        <feature version="[7,9)">jetty</feature>
 
        <bundle start-level="40">mvn:org.apache.cxf/cxf-rt-transports-http-jetty/3.0.4.redhat-621083</bundle>
 
    </feature>

We have to switch to Camel 2.16 (which will give us jclouds 1.9.1....) and get rid of Camel from Fuse 6.2.1.
